sql:
SELECT AVG(averageleadtime) AS average_delivery_time
FROM products
WHERE category = 'Electronics' AND standardprice > 100.00;

SELECT p.category, AVG(p.averageleadtime) AS average_lead_time
FROM products p
GROUP BY p.category;

external_knowledge:
- "Blossoms of products" refers to the products in the database;
- "Favored by customers" refers to the products with a total quantity ordered greater than 100;
- "Quantity they've gathered" refers to the total quantity ordered in the year 2023;
- "Average prices" refers to the average standard price of the products;
- "Longest time it takes for them to reach their admirers" refers to the maximum lead time for product delivery.

- 'Top 5 products by revenue' refers to the products with the highest total revenue from completed orders;
- Revenue is calculated by multiplying the quantity ordered by the standard price for each product;
- 'Completed' orders are those that have been successfully processed and delivered.

- "Plants" and "fruits" are metaphors for products and revenue, respectively;
- "Caretakers" are metaphors for suppliers;
- "Completed growth cycle" refers to orders with a status of 'Completed'.

- "Blossoming products" refers to the products that generate the highest revenue;
- "Garden of business entities" is a metaphorical representation of the collection of business entities in the database;
- "Top 5" indicates the first five products in the ranking by revenue.

- "Total quantity ordered" refers to the sum of all quantities of a product that have been ordered across all orders;
- "Average quantity ordered" is the mean quantity of a product ordered per order;
- "Order count" is the total number of orders placed for a product;
- "Total quantity on hand" is the sum of all quantities of a product currently available in the inventory;
- "Average quantity on hand" is the mean quantity of a product currently available in the inventory;
- "Minimum quantity on hand" is the lowest quantity of a product that has been recorded in the inventory;
- "Maximum quantity on hand" is the highest quantity of a product that has been recorded in the inventory.

- "Top 10 products by revenue" refers to the products with the highest total revenue generated from orders;
- "Total revenue" is calculated as the sum of the quantity ordered multiplied by the standard price of the product;
- "Average orders" refers to the average quantity of the product ordered across all orders.

- "Revenue" is often metaphorically compared to the "fruit of labor" in business contexts;
- "Last receipt cost" can be likened to the "seed" that was planted, representing the initial investment or cost;
- "Sweetness of the harvest" refers to the total revenue, with higher revenues being more "sweet" or profitable.

- "Completed orders" are those orders that have been fully processed and delivered;
- "Revenue percentage" is calculated as the revenue of a product divided by the total revenue of its category, multiplied by 100;
- "Total revenue" for a category is the sum of the revenues of all products in that category.
